### Payment Service API Testing
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code
### Replace placeholder values (marked with xxx) with actual values

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
@userId = user_123
@stripeCustomerId = cus_xxxxx
@paymentIntentId = pi_xxxxx
@transactionId = txn_xxxxx

### ========================================
### Customer Management
### ========================================

### 1. Create Stripe Customer
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "name": "Test User",
  "phone": "+1234567890"
}

### ========================================
### Payment Intents
### ========================================

### 2. Create Payment Intent
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/payment-intents
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "amount": 99.99,
  "currency": "usd",
  "stripeCustomerId": "{{stripeCustomerId}}",
  "orderId": "order_456",
  "description": "Test payment for order #456",
  "metadata": {
    "productId": "prod_123",
    "quantity": 2
  }
}

### 3. Confirm Payment Intent (Success)
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/payment-intents/confirm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "paymentIntentId": "{{paymentIntentId}}",
  "paymentMethodId": "pm_card_visa"
}

### 4. Confirm Payment Intent (Decline)
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/payment-intents/confirm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "paymentIntentId": "{{paymentIntentId}}",
  "paymentMethodId": "pm_card_chargeDeclined"
}

### 5. Confirm Payment Intent (Insufficient Funds)
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/payment-intents/confirm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "paymentIntentId": "{{paymentIntentId}}",
  "paymentMethodId": "pm_card_chargeDeclinedInsufficientFunds"
}

### ========================================
### Payment Methods
### ========================================

### 6. Attach Payment Method (Visa)
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/payment-methods/attach
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "paymentMethodId": "pm_card_visa",
  "stripeCustomerId": "{{stripeCustomerId}}"
}

### 7. Attach Payment Method (Mastercard)
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/payment-methods/attach
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "paymentMethodId": "pm_card_mastercard",
  "stripeCustomerId": "{{stripeCustomerId}}"
}

### ========================================
### Refunds
### ========================================

### 8. Create Full Refund
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/refunds
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "transactionId": "{{transactionId}}",
  "paymentIntentId": "{{paymentIntentId}}",
  "reason": "requested_by_customer",
  "metadata": {
    "refundedBy": "admin_123",
    "reason": "Customer request"
  }
}

### 9. Create Partial Refund
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/refunds
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "transactionId": "{{transactionId}}",
  "paymentIntentId": "{{paymentIntentId}}",
  "amount": 50.00,
  "reason": "requested_by_customer",
  "metadata": {
    "refundedBy": "admin_123",
    "reason": "Partial refund - damaged item"
  }
}

### ========================================
### Complete Test Flow
### ========================================

### Flow 1: Create customer
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "flow_test_001",
  "email": "flowtest@example.com",
  "name": "Flow Test User"
}

### Flow 2: Create payment intent (copy stripeCustomerId from previous response)
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/payment-intents
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "flow_test_001",
  "amount": 50.00,
  "currency": "usd",
  "stripeCustomerId": "cus_xxxxx",
  "orderId": "order_flow_001",
  "description": "Test flow payment"
}

### Flow 3: Confirm payment (copy paymentIntentId from previous response)
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/payment-intents/confirm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "paymentIntentId": "pi_xxxxx",
  "paymentMethodId": "pm_card_visa"
}

### Flow 4: Create refund (copy transactionId and paymentIntentId from previous responses)
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/refunds
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "transactionId": "txn_xxxxx",
  "paymentIntentId": "pi_xxxxx",
  "reason": "requested_by_customer"
}

### ========================================
### Webhook Testing (Manual)
### ========================================

### Webhook: Payment Intent Succeeded
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/webhooks
Content-Type: application/json
stripe-signature: test_signature

{
  "id": "evt_test_001",
  "object": "event",
  "type": "payment_intent.succeeded",
  "data": {
    "object": {
      "id": "{{paymentIntentId}}",
      "amount": 9999,
      "currency": "usd",
      "status": "succeeded",
      "latest_charge": "ch_test_001"
    }
  }
}

### Webhook: Payment Intent Failed
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/webhooks
Content-Type: application/json
stripe-signature: test_signature

{
  "id": "evt_test_002",
  "object": "event",
  "type": "payment_intent.payment_failed",
  "data": {
    "object": {
      "id": "{{paymentIntentId}}",
      "amount": 9999,
      "currency": "usd",
      "status": "requires_payment_method",
      "last_payment_error": {
        "message": "Your card was declined",
        "code": "card_declined"
      }
    }
  }
}

### ========================================
### Error Testing
### ========================================

### Error 1: Invalid Amount (Too Low)
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/payment-intents
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "amount": 0.25,
  "currency": "usd",
  "stripeCustomerId": "{{stripeCustomerId}}"
}

### Error 2: Missing Required Fields
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/payment-intents
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}"
}

### Error 3: Invalid Customer ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/payment-intents
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "amount": 99.99,
  "currency": "usd",
  "stripeCustomerId": "cus_invalid"
}

### Error 4: Refund Non-Existent Transaction
POST {{baseUrl}}/stripe/refunds
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "transactionId": "txn_nonexistent",
  "paymentIntentId": "pi_nonexistent",
  "reason": "requested_by_customer"
}

